mes at a time when pension systems worldwide are under increasing pressure due to rising life expectancy, increased governmental debt, uncertain economic conditions, and a global shift to defined contribution plans.&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=\\&quot;COLOR: #231f20; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\\&quot;COLOR: #231f20; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\\&quot;&gt;\\u201cThis research, through collaboration among Mercer consultants worldwide, the Victorian Government, and the Australian Centre for Financial Studies, benchmarks each country\\u2019s retirement income system, highlights shortcomings, and lists potential actions for improvement.\\u201d said David Knox, a Mercer Senior Partner and author of the study.&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=\\&quot;COLOR: #231f20; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\\&quot;&gt;\\u201cWorldwide, many of the challenges relating to aging populations are similar, irrespective of each country\\u2019s social, political,&amp;nbsp;historical, or economic influences,\\u201d he notes. \\u201cMany of the desirable policy reforms are also similar&amp;nbsp;and relate to pension ages, retirement level funding, work longevity, and benefit&amp;nbsp;design issues to reduce benefits leakage before retirement.\\u201d&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=\\&quot;COLOR: #231f20; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\\&quot;&gt;Learn more about the latest in global pension trends.&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/i&gt;&lt;\\/b&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=\\&quot;COLOR: #231f20; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\\&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=\\&quot;\\&quot; height=\\&quot;2433\\&quot; src=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/mthink.mercer.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2013\\/10\\/131014-MERCER-107-PENSIONINDEX.png\\&quot; width=\\&quot;500\\&quot; \\/&gt;&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/i&gt;&lt;\\/b&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=\\&quot;COLOR: #231f20; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Source: &lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/strong&gt;&lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/mthink.mercer.com\\/\\&quot;&gt;http:\\/\\/mthink.mercer.com&lt;\\/a&gt;&lt;\\/span&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n&quot;}', 1, '2014-07-11 10:18:59', '2014-07-11 10:18:59'),
(284, 1, 23, 4, 'insert', 'Steady Hiring and Compensation Ahead in Asia Pacific', '{&quot;category_id&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;ids&quot;:&quot;SSluVt1PgLc&quot;,&quot;name_vi&quot;:&quot;Steady Hiring and Compensation Ahead in Asia Pacific&quot;,&quot;slug_vi&quot;:&quot;steady-hiring-and-compensation-ahead-in-asia-pacific-SSluVt1PgLc&quot;,&quot;description_vi&quot;:&quot;In recent months, the global markets have hit a rough stretch, with stumbles in manufacturing and economic growth downgrades for most regions, even the once seemingly invincible Asian markets. Still, Mercer research and polling of HR leaders show a gradually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&quot;,&quot;content_vi&quot;:&quot;&lt;p style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;In recent months, the global markets have hit a rough stretch, with stumbles in manufacturing and economic growth downgrades for most regions, even the once seemingly invincible Asian markets. Still, &lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/www.mercer.com.hk\\/webcasts\\/2013-compensation-trends-in-asia-pacific\\&quot;&gt;Mercer research and polling of HR leaders&lt;\\/a&gt; show a gradually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;\\u201cNearly 50% of companies expect better business and financial performance in 2013, but anticipate that salary increase budgets will remain unchanged in 2013,\\u201d says Puneet Swani, Information Solutions and Rewards Practice Leader for Asia, Middle East, and Africa. \\u201cThis signals a very strong need for companies to visibly and effectively segment the workforce and allocate the limited reward investments to value creators.\\u201d&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Learn more about compensation trends in Asia.&lt;\\/i&gt;&lt;\\/b&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: center;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Click image to enlarge)&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: center;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/mthink.mercer.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2013\\/07\\/130716-MERCER-94-ASIACOMPENSATION.png\\&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=\\&quot;\\&quot; height=\\&quot;1200\\&quot; src=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/www.talentnet.vn\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/Image\\/information_center\\/news_event\\/130716-MERCER-94-ASIACOMPENSATION.png\\&quot; width=\\&quot;262\\&quot; \\/&gt;&lt;\\/a&gt;&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;Source: &lt;em&gt;mthink.mercer.com&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n&quot;,&quot;name_en&quot;:&quot;Steady Hiring and Compensation Ahead in Asia Pacific&quot;,&quot;slug_en&quot;:&quot;steady-hiring-and-compensation-ahead-in-asia-pacific--SSluVt1PgLc&quot;,&quot;description_en&quot;:&quot;In recent months, the global markets have hit a rough stretch, with stumbles in manufacturing and economic growth downgrades for most regions, even the once seemingly invincible Asian markets. Still, Mercer research and polling of HR leaders show a gradually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&quot;,&quot;content_en&quot;:&quot;&lt;p style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;In recent months, the global markets have hit a rough stretch, with stumbles in manufacturing and economic growth downgrades for most regions, even the once seemingly invincible Asian markets. Still, &lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/www.mercer.com.hk\\/webcasts\\/2013-compensation-trends-in-asia-pacific\\&quot;&gt;Mercer research and polling of HR leaders&lt;\\/a&gt; show a gradually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;\\u201cNearly 50% of companies expect better business and financial performance in 2013, but anticipate that salary increase budgets will remain unchanged in 2013,\\u201d says Puneet Swani, Information Solutions and Rewards Practice Leader for Asia, Middle East, and Africa. \\u201cThis signals a very strong need for companies to visibly and effectively segment the workforce and allocate the limited reward investments to value creators.\\u201d&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Learn more about compensation trends in Asia.&lt;\\/i&gt;&lt;\\/b&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: center;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Click image to enlarge)&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: center;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/mthink.mercer.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2013\\/07\\/130716-MERCER-94-ASIACOMPENSATION.png\\&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=\\&quot;\\&quot; height=\\&quot;1200\\&quot; src=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/www.talentnet.vn\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/Image\\/information_center\\/news_event\\/130716-MERCER-94-ASIACOMPENSATION.png\\&quot; width=\\&quot;262\\&quot; \\/&gt;&lt;\\/a&gt;&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;Source: &lt;em&gt;mthink.mercer.com&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n&quot;}', 1, '2014-07-11 10:20:22', '2014-07-11 10:20:22');
