(342, 1, 23, 4, 'edit', 'Steady Hiring and Compensation Ahead in Asia Pacific', '{&quot;category_id&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;ids&quot;:&quot;SSluVt1PgL&quot;,&quot;is_home&quot;:&quot;1&quot;,&quot;name_vi&quot;:&quot;Steady Hiring and Compensation Ahead in Asia Pacific&quot;,&quot;slug_vi&quot;:&quot;steady-hiring-and-compensation-ahead-in-asia-pacific-SSluVt1PgL&quot;,&quot;description_vi&quot;:&quot;In recent months, the global markets have hit a rough stretch, with stumbles in manufacturing and economic growth downgrades for most regions, even the once seemingly invincible Asian markets. Still, Mercer research and polling of HR leaders show a gradually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&quot;,&quot;content_vi&quot;:&quot;&lt;p style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;In recent months, the global markets have hit a rough stretch, with stumbles in manufacturing and economic growth downgrades for most regions, even the once seemingly invincible Asian markets. Still, &lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/www.mercer.com.hk\\/webcasts\\/2013-compensation-trends-in-asia-pacific\\&quot;&gt;Mercer research and polling of HR leaders&lt;\\/a&gt; show a gradually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;\\u201cNearly 50% of companies expect better business and financial performance in 2013, but anticipate that salary increase budgets will remain unchanged in 2013,\\u201d says Puneet Swani, Information Solutions and Rewards Practice Leader for Asia, Middle East, and Africa. \\u201cThis signals a very strong need for companies to visibly and effectively segment the workforce and allocate the limited reward investments to value creators.\\u201d&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-alig