adually improving global economy and continued moderate growth in Asia Pacific, leading to steady \\u2014 yet unremarkable compared to recent years \\u2014 growth in hiring.&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;\\u201cNearly 50% of companies expect better business and financial performance in 2013, but anticipate that salary increase budgets will remain unchanged in 2013,\\u201d says Puneet Swani, Information Solutions and Rewards Practice Leader for Asia, Middle East, and Africa. \\u201cThis signals a very strong need for companies to visibly and effectively segment the workforce and allocate the limited reward investments to value creators.\\u201d&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Learn more about compensation trends in Asia.&lt;\\/i&gt;&lt;\\/b&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: center;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Click image to enlarge)&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;div style=\\&quot;text-align: center;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/mthink.mercer.com\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2013\\/07\\/130716-MERCER-94-ASIACOMPENSATION.png\\&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=\\&quot;\\&quot; height=\\&quot;1200\\&quot; src=\\&quot;http:\\/\\/www.talentnet.vn\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/Image\\/information_center\\/news_event\\/130716-MERCER-94-ASIACOMPENSATION.png\\&quot; width=\\&quot;262\\&quot; \\/&gt;&lt;\\/a&gt;&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/div&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;p style=\\&quot;text-align: justify;\\&quot;&gt;Source: &lt;em&gt;mthink.mercer.com&lt;\\/em&gt;&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n&quot;}', 1, '2014-07-11 15:44:02', '2014-07-11 15:44:02'),
