ot;&gt;D\\u01b0\\u1edbi \\u0111\\u00e2y l\\u00e0 \\u0111i\\u1ec3m chu\\u1ea9n \\u0111\\u1ee3t 1 v\\u00e0o c\\u00e1c tr\\u01b0\\u1eddng THPT chuy\\u00ean v\\u00e0 tr\\u01b0\\u1eddng THPT c\\u00f3 l\\u1edbp chuy\\u00ean c\\u1ee7a H\\u00e0 N\\u1ed9i:&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n&quot;,&quot;name_en&quot;:&quot;Story&quot;,&quot;slug_en&quot;:&quot;story&quot;,&quot;content_en&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;Talentnet \\u2013 a Vietnamese company operating under License No. 4103007842 issued 18 September 2007 by DPI.&lt;\\/p&gt;\\n\\n&lt;ol&gt;\\n\\t&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talentnet \\u2013 formerly Human Resource Services of Pricewaterhouse Coopers Vietnam&lt;\\/strong&gt;, which operated throughout Indochina. This business has been a market leader in its sector for many years and PricewaterhouseCoopers was proud of the position it had achieved and its ability to provide outstanding services to clients.&amp;nbsp; Conflicts of interest meant that this executive recruitment service was not core to PwC Vietnam\\u2019s strategy going forward.&amp;nbsp; The Human Resource Services team enthusiastically grasped the challenge of taking on the ownership and development of this service in the Vietnamese market.&lt;\\/li&gt;\\n\\t&lt;li&gt;Ms. Tieu Yen Trinh, former Senior Manager of PricewaterhouseCoopers, who successfully led their Human Resource Services business for many years, took up the leadership of Talentnet, bringing with her the strong and experienced team from PricewaterhouseCoopers. Talentnet, with its mission to provide professional HR solutions to Vietnamese and international clients, is committed to continuous improvements in quality and takes seriously its responsibilities to society.&lt;\\/li&gt;\\n&lt;\\/ol&gt;\\n&quot;}', 1, '2014-07-18 17:37:01', '2014-07-18 17:37:01'),
